06/07/2007
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- High Representative Miroslav Lajcak made his first visit to Republika Srpska's (RS) capital on Friday (July 5th), saying BiH has no more time to lose due to personal confrontation, as it would only push the country into isolation. He called on RS and Federation of BiH leaders to reach compromise on key reforms, enabling the country to move forward and seal the Stabilisation and Association Agreement with the EU. In other news, EU Justice Commissioner Franco Frattini told visiting BiH Security Minister Tarik Sadovic that the Union and BiH would seal a visa liberalisation accord in September, so it could take effect in January. BiH, Albania and Montenegro initialled preliminary agreements with the EU in April. (Nezavisne Novine - 06/07/07; RTRS, NTV Hayat, Fena - 05/07/07)
